# understanding.mdc

## Project Name

Employee Performance Wins, Tasks & Reports Tracker

## Project Overview

The Employee Performance Wins, Tasks & Reports Tracker is a productivity and performance monitoring system that allows employers and employees to track work activities through tasks, daily reports, and achievements (wins).

The system begins with a **calendar-based interface** where both employees and employers can select a date to view or manage tasks, submit reports, and track performance.

Employers can create companies or teams and assign employees to them. Tasks created by employers remain **pending** until employees complete them. Employees also submit reports and record daily achievements.

---

# Core Objectives

1. Allow employers to assign and monitor tasks.
2. Allow employees to submit reports of daily work.
3. Track employee performance and wins.
4. Provide a date-based workflow using a calendar.
5. Support multiple companies or teams under one employer.

---

# System Roles

## 1. Employer (Admin)

Employer has full control of the system.

Capabilities:

* Create Companies or Teams
* Invite or register employees
* Assign tasks
* Review employee reports
* Approve or comment on reports
* Monitor employee progress
* View employee wins and productivity analytics

---

## 2. Employee

Employees interact mainly with their assigned tasks and daily reports.

Capabilities:

* View assigned tasks
* Mark tasks as completed
* Submit daily reports
* Record achievements (wins)
* View tasks and reports by calendar date

---

# Core System Interface

## Calendar Dashboard (Main Interface)

The first interface users see after login.

Features:

* Monthly calendar view
* Users can click any date
* Clicking a date opens the **Task & Report Page**

Purpose:
To organize work activities by date.

Example Flow:

User Login → Calendar Dashboard → Select Date → Task & Report Page

---

# Task & Report Page

When a date is selected from the calendar, the system opens a page containing:

### 1. Tasks Section

Displays tasks assigned by the employer.

Fields:

* Task Title
* Task Description
* Assigned By
* Assigned Date
* Status

Task Status Types:

* Pending
* In Progress
* Completed

Rules:

* Tasks created by employer remain **Pending**
* Task remains pending until employee marks it **Completed**
* Unfinished tasks **remain visible and accumulate until completed**

---

### 2. Report Submission

Employees must submit reports for selected dates.

Report Fields:

* Report Title
* Work Done
* Challenges Faced
* Achievements (Wins)
* Attachments (optional)
* Submission Time

Reports are submitted to the employer for review.

Employer Actions:

* Approve Report
* Comment on Report
* Request Revision

---

### 3. Wins / Achievements Section

Employees can record daily achievements.

Examples:

* Completed important task
* Reached milestone
* Solved major issue

Fields:

* Win Title
* Description
* Date
* Related Task (optional)

Purpose:
To highlight productivity and employee impact.

---

# Company / Team Management

Employers can create organizational structures.

Structure:

Employer
└── Company
└── Teams
└── Employees

Employer Capabilities:

* Create Company
* Create Teams
* Assign Employees to Teams
* Move employees between teams

---

# Task Assignment System

Employer creates tasks.

Task Fields:

* Task Title
* Description
* Assigned Employee
* Assigned Team (optional)
* Start Date
* Due Date
* Priority Level

Priority Levels:

* Low
* Medium
* High
* Critical

Rules:

* Tasks remain **Pending** until employee completes them
* Overdue tasks are highlighted
* Tasks accumulate until completed

---

# Reports Management

Employees submit reports tied to a specific date.

Report Status:

* Submitted
* Reviewed
* Approved
* Needs Revision

Employer Dashboard shows:

* Reports awaiting review
* Employee report history
* Productivity insights

---

# Notifications

System sends notifications for:

Employees:

* New task assigned
* Task deadline approaching
* Employer comments on report

Employers:

* New report submitted
* Task completed
* Employee win recorded

Notification Channels:

* Email
* In-app notifications

---

# Performance Tracking

System calculates performance indicators.

Metrics include:

* Tasks completed
* Pending tasks
* Daily reports submitted
* Wins recorded
* Completion rate

Employers can view:

* Employee performance summary
* Team productivity
* Company-wide statistics

